cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of generating semantic layout from scene graph, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses sequence to sequence (seq-to-seq) learning, which is a popular technique in NLP, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a new metric for evaluating the task, which involves measuring spatial distribution, indicating that it could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the task of translating between two different vocabularies, which could also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
